Sentencas: Upon reduction and re-oxidization, the interface of a microtubular solid oxide fuel cell (MTSOFC) anode/electrolyte was structurally analyzed using a dual beam focused ion beam/scanning electron microscope (FIB/SEM) and scanning transmission electron microscopy combined with energy dispersive X-ray spectrometer (STEM-EDX).
Titulo: Dimensional analysis of Ni-NiO grains at anode/electrolyte interface for SOFC during redox reaction

Sentencas: The bulk volume of the dense NiO phase dramatically contracted upon reduction, while the YSZ phases are completely unaffected.
Titulo: Dimensional analysis of Ni-NiO grains at anode/electrolyte interface for SOFC during redox reaction

Sentencas: No cracks or particle detachment are observed either at the interface of the anode/electrolyte or in the anode backbone.
Titulo: Dimensional analysis of Ni-NiO grains at anode/electrolyte interface for SOFC during redox reaction

Sentencas: Compared with the initial NiO state (as-prepared), the area of Ni phase contracts by 22.6%-83.7%, depending on the grain size.
Titulo: Dimensional analysis of Ni-NiO grains at anode/electrolyte interface for SOFC during redox reaction
